(113, '4', 'Journal Article', NULL, '1,2', 'A simplified non-linear hydraulic diffusivity model based on normalised sorptivity', 'Sādhanā', '', '', '2023-06-09', '', 'Springer', '', 'https://doi.org/10.1007/s12046-023-02152-w', '', '', '48', '100, 2023', '<p>The inverse modelling of moisture dependent hydraulic diffusivity function for porous building materials either requires the non-destructive measurement of water absorption profiles with expensive equipment or a tedious training of model parameters to optimally capture the gravimetric properties. This study proposes a one-parameter non-linear hydraulic diffusivity model that can be calibrated for a porous building material if its normalised sorptivity as determined through simple gravimetric experimentation is known. The approach adopted combines a novel characteristic moisture profile function with Boltzmann-Matano&rsquo;s equation to obtain an analytical model for hydraulic diffusivity. The model has been validated through the simulation of water absorption profiles reported in independent experimental investigations and of the moisture content observed in laboratory experiments. The results of validation, sensitivity analysis and comparison with the commonly used two-parameter exponential model are indicative of the robustness of the proposed model for a wide range of porous materials.</p>\r\n', '', 'On My Page', '1', '2'),
